cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.HC, cs.CL, cs.CY 

This paper is likely to belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category as it deals with improving tag recommendations, which is a common task in information retrieval. It also involves modeling cognitive processes, which is related to the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-category. The Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-category is also likely as the paper deals with social tagging and collective macro-level processes. The Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category is relevant as the paper deals with natural language processing in the form of assigning tags to resources. Finally, the Cybernetics (cs.CY) sub-category is relevant as the paper deals with modeling complex systems involving human cognition and social dynamics.
